# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Environment variable template — VARIABLE NAMES ONLY, NEVER VALUES.
#
# Real values are NEVER pasted into chat, source code, docs, tests, or
# commits. Add them to your runtime environment (e.g. the Claude Code
# Cloud Environment's environment-variable settings, or a local .env
# file that is excluded by .gitignore).
#
# This file is intentionally almost empty: no broker has been chosen yet
# (Phase 0 in progress), so no credential variables are defined yet.
# Broker/data variables will be added in the security-design phase and
# Phase 4, with separate variables per environment (dev / paper / live)
# and per purpose (market data vs. order placement).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Runtime environment. The application must refuse to start in any mode
# it cannot independently verify. Live mode additionally requires the
# multi-step enablement procedure in docs/bot_constitution.md.
# Allowed values: development | testing | paper
TRADING_ENV=development
